  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To study the effects of a low free sugar diet on lipid profile, glycemic indices, liver
      enzymes, inflammatory factors and hepatic steatosis and fibrosis in patients with
      Nonalcoholic fatty liver disease, 50 patients who referred to Gastrointestinal (GI) clinic
      with steatosis grade 2 and 3 will be randomly allocated to receive low free sugar diet or
      regular diet for 12 weeks; both groups will be advised to adherence the investigators'
      nutrition recommendation and exercise program too. At the first and the end of the
      intervention, lipid profiles, liver enzymes,glycemic indices, some inflammatory markers, and
      liver fibrosis will be assessed and compared between groups.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
